<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1577,1710]" pageId="9" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,1577,1602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="314">Discussion.</emphasis>
Most specimens fit the diagnosis proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Deharveng" box="[865,1076,1577,1601]" pageId="9" pageNumber="314" refString="Deharveng, L. (1982) A propos des Folsomia du groupe quadrioculata Tullberg, 1871. Revue d'Ecologie et de Biologie du Sol, 19, 613 - 627." type="journal article" year="1982">
Deharveng (
<number box="[1010,1068,1577,1601]" pageId="9" pageNumber="314" value="1982.0">1982</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for the 
<taxonomicName box="[1186,1436,1577,1601]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="9" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manolachei">
<emphasis box="[1186,1436,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="314">Folsomia manolachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. In the alpine zone of Khamar Daban the pale form with pigmentation only on the ocelli is common. In lower altitudes, normal grey form occurs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1372,1685,1710]" pageId="9" pageNumber="314" type="distribution">
